      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The *result* of silencing dissent is censorship, regardless of the initial intent of the critique. However, the \"progress\" side is inherently more legitimate because the goal of social justice movements is to correct demonstrable, real-world harms like racism and sexism. When the focus shifts from correcting harm to policing speech, then the movement has become authoritarian, but the initial drive for equity remains morally sound.",
